  "tipTitle1": "pH Control",
  "tipDesc1": "Keep your pool's pH between 7.2 and 7.6 for crystal clear and safe water. Check it at least 2-3 times per week.",
  "tipTitle2": "Filter Cleaning",
  "tipDesc2": "Clean filters regularly according to type. A clean filter ensures good water circulation and reduces energy consumption.",
  "tipTitle3": "Post-Rain Hygiene",
  "tipDesc3": "After heavy rains, increase disinfection and check chlorine levels. Rain dilutes chemicals.",
  "tipTitle4": "Water Circulation",
  "tipDesc4": "Keep the pump running at least 4-6 hours daily in winter and 8-10 hours in summer for good circulation.",
  "tipTitle5": "Total Alkalinity",
  "tipDesc5": "Keep alkalinity between 80-120 ppm. This stabilizes pH and improves chemical efficiency.",
  "tipTitle6": "Liner Protection",
  "tipDesc6": "Avoid leaving sharp or pointed objects in the pool. Use a liner protector under the water.",
  "tipTitle7": "Liner Cleaning",
  "tipDesc7": "Clean the liner with a soft brush regularly to prevent algae buildup. Avoid abrasive products.",
  "tipTitle8": "Winter Maintenance",
  "tipDesc8": "In winter, cover the pool to protect the liner. Use a special winter cover or blanket.",
  "tipTitle9": "Waterproofing",
  "tipDesc9": "Regularly check that the coating has no cracks. Repair small cracks before they get bigger.",
  "tipTitle10": "Coating Maintenance",
  "tipDesc10": "Clean walls regularly with a brush to prevent stains and algae. The coating lasts longer with good maintenance.",
  "tipTitle11": "Joint Sealing",
  "tipDesc11": "Periodically check joint sealing. Re-seal if necessary to prevent leaks.",
  "tipTitle12": "Chlorine Control",
  "tipDesc12": "Keep free chlorine between 1.0-3.0 ppm. Low levels favor algae, high levels irritate eyes and skin.",
  "tipTitle13": "Combined Chlorine",
  "tipDesc13": "If combined chlorine exceeds 0.5 ppm, apply shock treatment. This improves water quality.",
  "tipTitle14": "Chlorine Addition",
  "tipDesc14": "Add chlorine in the afternoon/evening to better utilize its disinfection. Sun reduces effectiveness during the day.",
  "tipTitle15": "Correct Salinity",
  "tipDesc15": "Keep salinity between 2700-3400 ppm depending on the electrolyzer type. More salt improves disinfection.",
  "tipTitle16": "Cell Cleaning",
  "tipDesc16": "Clean the electrolysis cell every 3-6 months to maintain efficiency. Use diluted muriatic acid.",
  "tipTitle17": "Cell Calcification",
  "tipDesc17": "If the cell calcifies, chlorine production decreases. Regular cleaning prevents this.",
  "tipTitle18": "Sand Backwashing",
  "tipDesc18": "Perform backwashing when pressure rises 8-10 psi above normal working pressure.",
  "tipTitle19": "Sand Replacement",
  "tipDesc19": "Change sand every 5-7 years. Old sand loses filtration capacity.",
  "tipTitle20": "Multiport Valve",
  "tipDesc20": "Keep the multiport valve in FILTER position during normal operation. Check its operation regularly.",
  "tipTitle21": "Cartridge Cleaning",
  "tipDesc21": "Clean the cartridge with high pressure water every 2 weeks or when pressure rises. Avoid chemicals.",
  "tipTitle22": "Cartridge Replacement",
  "tipDesc22": "Replace the cartridge every 1-2 years or when it doesn't maintain adequate pressure. New cartridges improve filtration.",
  "tipTitle23": "Storage",
  "tipDesc23": "Store spare cartridges in a dry place. Avoid direct sunlight that damages the material.",
  "tipTitle24": "Diatomaceous Earth Recharge",
  "tipDesc24": "Recharge with diatomaceous earth every 2-3 weeks or after backwashing.",
  "tipTitle25": "Frequent Backwashing",
  "tipDesc25": "Diatomaceous earth filters require more frequent backwashing. Do it when pressure rises 7-8 psi.",
  "tipTitle26": "Diatomaceous Earth Handling",
  "tipDesc26": "Use a mask when handling diatomaceous earth. Avoid inhaling dust to protect your lungs.",
  "tipTitle27": "Maintenance Record",
  "tipDesc27": "Keep a record of measurements and treatments. This helps identify patterns and problems.",
  "tipTitle28": "Complete Water Test",
  "tipDesc28": "Perform a complete water test (pH, chlorine, alkalinity, hardness) at least once a week.",
  "tipTitle29": "Algae Prevention",
  "tipDesc29": "Keep chlorine and pH at correct levels to prevent algae. It's easier to prevent than to cure.",
  "tipTitle30": "UV Protector",
  "tipDesc30": "Use chlorine stabilizer (cyanuric acid) to protect against UV radiation. Dose according to instructions.",
